{"id":"learn_001","lesson":"Confidence markers must be grounded in actual verification, not just self-assessment","context":"Markers without source tracking are not trustworthy","created_at":"2026-04-24T05:04:00Z"}
{"id":"learn_002","lesson":"Self-critic can only catch detectable errors - it has blind spots for language processing errors","context":"Chinese chars error was not caught by self-critic because it wasn't a confidence-level issue","created_at":"2026-04-24T16:38:00Z"}
{"id":"learn_003","lesson":"Verification-first > generate-first - verify claims before outputting","context":"Hallucination risk reduced by checking sources before making claims","created_at":"2026-04-24T16:38:00Z"}
{"id":"learn_004","lesson":"External measurement beats internal self-assessment - use calibration tracking","context":"I cannot access my own uncertainty state directly, but I can measure it via logged predictions and outcomes","created_at":"2026-04-24T16:38:00Z"}
{"id":"learn_005","lesson":"Cross-session memory requires file-based persistence, not internal context","context":"Learn store and truth repo persist across sessions; internal context does not","created_at":"2026-04-24T16:38:00Z"}
